w kinetic equation is applied for the calculation\nof the neutrino asymmetry accounting for the Berry curvature and the\nelectroweak interaction with background fermions in the Higgs phase. Such an\ninteraction generates a neutrino asymmetry through the electroweak coupling of\nneutrino currents with electromagnetic fields in plasma, which is $\\sim\nG_\\mathrm{F}^2$. It turns out that this effect is especially efficient for\nmaximally helical magnetic fields.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Dec 2017 18:20:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-27"}
